In this assignment, simple transformations on data is performed in following steps:
1)	
a) Create a new table for the analysis call “sales_genre”.  
b) Load the table “sales” into this table.
c) Select these columns: Genre, Global_Sales, Critic_Score.   
2)  Round the data found in the “Global_Sales” column. 
3) Filter the data to only look at those items in the “Critic_Score” column that are greater than 0.
4) Order the data in the “Critic_Score” column from highest to lowest. 
